OL,3,C'Revolutionary' device to tackle acid
OL,4,Creflux given to first UK patients
OL,6,FIt happens when the muscular valve `
OL,7,Fthe lower oesophageal sphincter ` at
OL,8,Fthe bottom of the oesophagus becomes
OL,9,Fweakened because it has moved too
OL,10,Fclose to the diaphragm or even into
OL,11,Fthe chest which affects its function
OL,12,Fto allow food in and stop acid leaking
OL,13,Fout.
OL,15,FThis can result in a range of symptoms
OL,16,Fincluding heartburn, regurgitation,
OL,17,Fdifficulty swallowing, bloating,
OL,18,Fexcessive salivation, coughing, nausea
OL,19,Fand a hoarse voice, as well as teeth
OL,20,Fand gum damage, nutritional problems,
OL,21,Fand sleep impairment.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
